WeRateDogs Analysis using Twitter data¶

@WeRateDogs is a twitter account that provides "professional dog ratings" since November 2015 boasting 9.3 million followers and a lot of media attention. The project at hand focuses on gathering the @WeRateDogs archive data, favorites and retweets count annd image predictions up until August 2017. The information collected would provide analytical insights into the various activities on the @WeRateDogs account.

The data gathered were assessed for quality and tidiness issues and were cleaned resulting in a dataframe with 1030 rows and 13 columns(tweet_id, favorite_counts, retweet_counts, name, dog_stage, dog_breed, etc). The name and dog_stage columns contain many 'None' aand null values, that were converted to empty strings. They are presented in the analyses as the most predominant names and/or dog stage.

When these empty name strings in the name and dog _stage columns of the dataframe are not included in the analyses, then we get a slightly different picture from the cells that are not empty.

The most and least common dog names were documented by obtaining the top 10 value_counts for each of the dog names.

* The most common dog name was Cooper and some of the least common were Fizz and Superpup (so cute!!!)
![image-2.png](attachment:image-2.png)
![image-3.png](attachment:image-3.png)

The most popular dog names were based on the retweets and favorite counts.

* Stephan was the most retweeted dog name, and Bo was the most favouritted dog name.
![image-4.png](attachment:image-4.png)

Most of the featured dogs were categorized as Pupper, based on the @WeRateDogs dogtionary. The Pupper dog stage was also the most favourited dog stage (who doesnt love a good Pupper?!!) and Doggo was the most retweeted stage. There were dogs alloted two dog stages such as Doggo, Pupper, Doggo, Floofer, Doggo, Puppo, I reckon these display double dose of 'duteness' (dog-cuteness).....1000/10!!!

The dog breeds were based on a neural network breed prediction of the dog images, collected from the @WeRateDogs. So what dog breed were most popular based on the favorite and retweets? (I asked the same question. Lol!). The beautiful golden haired and very playful Golden retriever was the most popular dog breed, along with the Pembroke, Labrador retriever, Chihuahua (no surpise here!) and French bulldog.

The @WeRateDogs twitter is a 'happy hormone' booster for sure and the analyses provide possible insights into the names of that are most favoured by 'dog parents' and the breeds that are most favoured by everyone. @WeRateDogs also provides ratings for the featured dogs, and these information is not considered in this analysis, but would be interesting to explore in future analysis.

In conclusion, adopt a dog and improve the quality of life!
